Description: Foot and lower wall of East Greek pottery cup or bowl with sharply profiled flaring ring foot; brown clay with white inclusions; glaze fired light to mid-brown interior glazed with added red disc and band on floor; exterior: glaze on outer face of foot and resting surface; reserved underside; inscription cut on inside of foot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 462)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 204)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.173)
